cybox:Observable.cybox:Description: This CGI script is a Pulse Secure file, maliciously modified by the attacker to siphon login credentials to a file named "dswebserver.statementcounters", stored in the /tmp directory of the compromised Pulse Secure device. The malicious code starts from "my $uf=" and ends at "close (*FN);" (Figure 1 and 2).

stix:Incident.incident:Title: 10334057.r3.v1
stix:Incident.incident:Description:
##### Incident Summary #####
None
##### Report Summary #####
CISA received one Common Gateway Interface (CGI) script for analysis. The CGI script is a Pulse Secure file, maliciously modified to siphon login credentials to a file stored in the /tmp directory on the compromised Pulse Secure device. This analysis is derived from malicious files found on Pulse Connect Secure devices.
##### Conclusion #####
None
##### Mitigation #####
None
